SIMPLE: rover
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Rover
<hw>Rov"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[D. <ets>roover</ets> a
robber. See <er>Rove</er>, <pos>v. i.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One
who practices robbery on the seas; a pirate.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Yet Pompey the Great deserveth honor more justly for scouring the
seas, and taking from the <qex>rovers</qex> 846 sail of ships.</q>
<rj><qau>Holland.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One who wanders about by sea or land; a wanderer; a
rambler.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Hence, a fickle, inconstant person.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <fld>(Croquet)</fld> <def>A ball which has passed through
all the hoops and would go out if it hit the stake but is continued in
play; also, the player of such a ball.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <fld>(Archery)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>Casual marks at
uncertain distances.</def> <rj><au>Encyc. Brit.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sd>(b)</sd> <def>A sort of arrow.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>All sorts, flights, <qex>rovers</qex>, and butt shafts.</q>
<rj><qau>B. Jonson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<cs><p><col><b>At rovers</b></col>, <cd>at casual marks; hence, at
random; <as>as, shooting <ex>at rovers</ex></as>. See def. 5
<sd>(a)</sd> above.</cd> <au>Addison.</au>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Bound down on every side with many bands because it shall not run
<qex>at rovers</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Robynson (More's Utopia).</qau></rj>
⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p></cs>

<p><ent>Roving</ent>⟦br⟧
